OTA_ReadRQ

Message Description

The purpose of this document is, to define and describe the messages to be used in protel.I/O to lookup or validate checked in guests and future reservations via protel.I/O. This functionality can be used by several systems:

  • users at POS systems can lookup guests with different parameters -  The reservation number of a found guest can be used as a referral in a guest transfer payment being part of an invoice mirror transaction

  • SPA and POS systems can validate guests by reading information from an electronic key provided to a guest for his stay- via reservation number written onto the key

  • Internet authentication systems can authenticate guests by validating information entered by them on a logon page, they were redirected to in their browser. Acquired information with the logon is a combination of information: reservation number, last name, first name, etc. depending on the systems possibilities and configuration. The guest can be found with a lookup where some of the information is provided in the lookup request while other - especially various optional logon parameters - are tried to be found in the replied list of guests



Note:

These tables show the attributes that protel uses. Please pay attention to attributes marked as available in OnPrem and not available in protel AIR or the other way round. Functionality enhancements are ongoing. So it is important to frequently check this site for updates.

0..1

To indicate if a list should always be returned even when only one reservation matches the input criteria. The default is to return the reservation record. If set to true, then always return a list.

  • @ReturnListIndicator="true" then all the search filters will be applied as "like" search criteria.

OTA_ReadRQ

Message Description

The purpose of this document is, to define and describe the messages to be used in protel.I/O to lookup or validate checked in guests and future reservations via protel.I/O. This functionality can be used by several systems:

  • users at POS systems can lookup guests with different parameters -  The reservation number of a found guest can be used as a referral in a guest transfer payment being part of an invoice mirror transaction

  • SPA and POS systems can validate guests by reading information from an electronic key provided to a guest for his stay- via reservation number written onto the key

  • Internet authentication systems can authenticate guests by validating information entered by them on a logon page, they were redirected to in their browser. Acquired information with the logon is a combination of information: reservation number, last name, first name, etc. depending on the systems possibilities and configuration. The guest can be found with a lookup where some of the information is provided in the lookup request while other - especially various optional logon parameters - are tried to be found in the replied list of guests



Note:

These tables show the attributes that protel uses. Please pay attention to attributes marked as available in OnPrem and not available in protel AIR or the other way round. Functionality enhancements are ongoing. So it is important to frequently check this site for updates.
